{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_geranium_ver02/data/sn84028102/00340580813/1957082201/0526.xml":{"full_text":"To Complete Water St\nResurfacing by Oct. 31\nResurfacing of Water St. and\nstreets around the park in Char\ndon Village is expected to be\ncompleted by October 31, accor\nding to an announcement made\ntoday by the Ohio Department\nof Highways.\nThe section of Water St. from\nthe railroad tracks to the park,\nwhich motorists have found to\nbe one of the jumpiest stretch\nes of street in the village, has\nnot been resurfaced for at least\nnine years.\nThe last paving of this sec\ntion of the street occurred so\nlong ago that the record of\nwork done are no longer on\nin the Cleveland office of\nstate highway department.\nthe\nfile\nthe\nThe other section of Water\nSt., from the railroad tracks\nwest to the village corporation\nline, is comparatively smooth\nWEIL PROVE\nYOU CAN\nWITH\nCovers More\nCosts Less\nProtects Longer\nAnother\ntraveling. It was resurfaced\nboth in 1948 and 1953.\nThe apparent low bid for the\npresent work, which includes\nE. Park St. and Main St. in ad\ndition to Water St., is $39,795.80.\nsubmitted by the William L.\nSchloss Paving Co. of Cleve\nland\nThe state department estima\nted the work would cost $38,000.\nChardon taxpayers will direct\nly foot $3000 of the paving bill.\nAt its July meeting counucil ap\nproved the expenditure, as re\nquested by the state, calling it\na bargain. \u201cLet\u2019s sign the con\ntract before they change their\nminds,\u201d one council member\ncommented at the time.\nThe resurfacing will be done\nwith asphaltic concrete. Total\nlength is almost one mile.\nHOW TO SAVE ON HOUSE PAINTING\nand a ho.t of modern cefors\nChardon Plaza\n.s 3S.?. y ,..v v?\nloads of wash\na day!\nIt\u2019s possible with\nand gel new beauty for your home too!\nSabSandies Hear\nHealth, Safety Talk\nThe eleventh meeting of the\nChardon Sal-Sandies was held\nAugust 5 at Kay Wollpert\u2019s house\nat 3:00 p.m.\nMrs. Thayer was our 