ed in the county.\u201ds mun\nicipalities was found to be in\nChardon, Middlefield and Burton\nwhere there were 1.803 734 and\n669 respectively.\nThere were 14,472 vehicles reg\nistered in the conuty from out\nside the various municipalities.\nractors&lmplements\nHomelite Chain Saws\nTIRES TUBES\nBATTERIES\nGENERAL RE1 mIRING\nNewbury Auto Service\nNewbury, Ohio Ph. 520\nMil:\nwhen you use an electric water heater of\n30-gallon capacity or more. For full information, call your nearest\nIlluminating Company office.\nALWAYS AT YOUR SERVICE IM THE BEST '.OCATION IN THE NATION\n(Jitj\nCamp Fire Girls\nSeek Geauga Leaders\nCHESTER The Cleveland jectives.\nCouncil of Camp Fire Girls Is 2. A minimum age of 21 years,\nbusy combing the community 3. Completion of the Basic\nfor teachers, librarians and oth\ner persons who have had exper\ni ience in teaching or leading\ngroups or individuals who po\nssess some special skill which\nthey would like to share with\n\u2019others, according to Mrs. A. R. I\nMueller, publicity director for\nthe West Geauga group.\nFire organization and its ob-\nLETTERS\nto the\nEDITOR\n\"C' w I \u2018CD\nJL'L-- 1 1 ELI\\3\ntO tnC\nhl JI I (JR\nEditor, Geauga Record:\nI would like to clear a few\nmisconceptions which I fear may\nhave arisen in Geauga County.\nTOPS (Take Off Pounds Sen\nsibly* is a national organization.!\nIt is non-profit, non-sectarian,\nnon-political. It is approved and\nencouraged by the American\nMedical Association and doctors\neverywhere.\nThe founder of TOPS national,\nMrs. Esther Manz of Milwaukee,\nwas aided by a doctor when\nshe started the first club.\nSince diet and weight reduc\ning regulations are definitely a\npersonal and individual prob\nlem, each club member has to\nhave her own health directions\nset up by her family physjeian.\nThe club works on the idea of\ngroup therapy for the obese,\nmuch as the AA works for the\nalcoholic.\nEvery TOPS club must be\nauthorized through national\nheadquarters. All TOPS materi\nals are copyrighted and regis\ntered in Washington and cannot\nbe copied or used.\nThere is at the present time\none TOPS club in Geauga Coun\nty. It is called the \u201cGeauga\nMelting Pots.\u201d The leader is\nMrs. Rose Vargo of Novelty\nThe group is for women only.\nIf there is a man interested\nin starting a group, I w\u2019ould like\nto have him contact me.\nIf any women are interested\nin joining a club or becoming\nthe leader of a club they can\nwrite to me directly or call me.\nIt has been called to my at\ntention that there are several\nclubs in Geauga County which\nare using the name TOPS. The\nletter is self-explanitory. I felt\nthis was a nice\nthem to change\ntheir clubs.\nway to warn\nthe name of\nThank you,\nMrs. Colleen\n114 Brooksdale Rd.\nLamprecht\nPainesville, Ohio.\nHave You Met\nMr. and Mrs. Walter Crago of\nChardon-Madison Rd. who mov\ned to Chardon from Spangler,\nPa.? Mr. Crago is Spec. 3rd\nclass in the Army (paratrooper)\nstationed in German. Mrs. Cra\ngo works in the office at Snap\nout Forms.\nSubscribe and Save!\nTHE RECORD, CHARDON, OHIO, AUGUST 22, 1957\u201411\nTraining Course for Leaders,\nor comparable training,\nindicated above).\n4. Competence in a skill\nthe ability to teach it to\ners or the potential for de\nveloping this ability.\nThe Camp Fire organization\nbelieves that by utilizing the ab-\nIn August, those who qualify uties of volunteers it can make\nn eiuVt training more readily available\nto leaders.\ncourse which will enable them\nto teach all or part of Camp\nFire\u2019s Basic Training Course\nfor Leaders to prospective lead\ners. Florence Craig, Director of\nAdult Education for the Cuya\nhoga Library, will conduct the\nsessions. Those who wish to ap-,\nply should have the following\u2019\nqualifications: -g O 1\n1 Evidence of a strong, posi- (.QOfclP OCnCLltS\ntive feeling for the Camp vJVVHlV UCUV UV11VL1L3\n\u201cCHAD\u201d\nStudents Get\nScholarships\n(Ajs\nand\noth-\nApplications can be obtained\nfrom the Clevelan